Class TextTypesPlanner

java.lang.Object
  WYSIWYM.transformer.ContentPlanner
      WYSIWYM.testclasses.TextTypesPlanner

public class TextTypesPlanner
extends ContentPlanner

Acts as a ContentPlanner, but plans two different text types, that use no syntactic aggregation. This class was used only for the text comparison experiment.

Version:
1.0 22-01-2009

lexicalise

protected List<DependencyTreeTransformer> lexicalise(SGNode topic,
                                                     List<SGEdge> edges,
                                                     int condition)
Lexicalises all edges of this node that haven't been added to a previous paragraph, and returns a list with the resulting dependency trees. Unlike the contentplanner, this class does not use relative clauses, but they are planned when the paragraphs are assigned; so when a relative clause comes along, we need to lexicalise it here and add it to this paragraph.

Parameters:
topic - SGNode topic of the paragraph
Returns:
List
